This folder (development) should not be included in any deployment.

The committed versions of index.html and iguana.html include the minified / compiled JS and CSS files. For development, you will need to replace those with the below list.

If you make changes to the JS or CSS files used, update the list here and in the makefile.

To generate the minified / compiled files, run 'make' in the development folder. It should produce the files and place them one directory up alongside index.html.

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/jquery-ui-1.10.3.custom.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/datatables/jquery.dataTables.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/datatables/TableTools.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/help_popup/help_popup.css" />
	
    <!-- For index.html:    <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/licensing.css" /> -->
    <!-- For iguana.html: <link rel="stylesheet" href="development/iguana.css" /> -->

